{
  "stem": "12674.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Or the bale, you had to go, you know, put it with your hook and go up with the bale.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "The-- the bales weighed 90 kilos, which is 200 pounds, and I weighed approximately 95 pounds at the time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I was 14 years old.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And the baskets weighed about 60 kilos, which is, I don't know, 150 pounds, something like that, give or take a couple of pounds.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "It doesn't pay to figure it out too exactly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And that was my life.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And every evening I went home, and every morning I went.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And we sat there in snow.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And sometimes it would take us two hours in the wagon to get there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And we sat there in the back of the wagon in snow and rain and summer, winter.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And that's why today I have scoliosis in two places, a misplaced vertebrae, and I'm-- my-- my-- my body's twisted like a pretzel.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I was carrying twice my own weight for two years.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The first time I picked it up, I-- they put a-- a thing on-- on-- on me, and I flew back.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I made a somersault in back over the basket, because I was-- it was much too heavy for me.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How was I able to carry?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I learned how because I knew I had to.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And if I didn't carry it, somebody was going to hit me, so I carried it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I did one step at a time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And somebody says, don't do this and don't breathe like that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- I don't know, I did.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I became as strong as an ox.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was very, very strong at that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was young, and I was healthy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the physical exercise, aside from the fact that it ruined my bones, didn't-- didn't do me any harm.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
